{"key":"post-15530571","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>15530571</id>\n<content>The salt test has long been disproved for our use growing mushrooms.&amp;nbsp; Hygrometers, when they're accurate at all, are only accurate through a very small portion of the scale.&amp;nbsp; This is why cigar aficionados use the salt method, but mushroom growers use the damp towel method.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Furthermore, if a hygrometer is off by 20% at one part of the scale, it's not going to be off by that same 20% at another part of the scale.&amp;nbsp; You can't simply add or subtract the difference.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>15530572</next>\n<prev>15530558</prev>\n<first>15530558</first>\n<last>15530585</last>\n<when>1324151336</when>\n<utime>12/17/11 09:48 PM</utime>\n</post>"}